, delete etc.) the particular fields of the data being processed via external configuration. It's as simple as adding a new transform to the transforms section of the particular connector configuration file:"},"507":{"id":"/docs/connectors/sdk-15","page_id":"/docs/connectors/sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/connectors/sdk#protocol-buffers-support","content":"The SDK includes support for Protocol Buffers (protobuf) format with both encoding and decoding capabilities. Protocol Buffers provide efficient serialization and are particularly useful for high-performance data streaming scenarios."},"508":{"id":"/docs/connectors/sdk-16","page_id":"/docs/connectors/sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/connectors/sdk#configuration-example","content":"Here's a complete example configuration for using Protocol Buffers with Iggy connectors."},"509":{"id":"/docs/connectors/sdk-17","page_id":"/docs/connectors/sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/connectors/sdk#configuration-example","content":"Main runtime config (config.toml):"},"510":{"id":"/docs/connectors/sdk-18","page_id":"/docs/connectors/sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/connectors/sdk#configuration-example","content":"Source connector config (connectors/protobuf_source.toml):"},"511":{"id":"/docs/connectors/sdk-19","page_id":"/docs/connectors/sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/connectors/sdk#configuration-example","content":"Sink connector config (connectors/protobuf_sink.toml):"},"512":{"id":"/docs/connectors/sdk-20","page_id":"/docs/connectors/sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/connectors/sdk#source-configuration","content":"schema_path: Path to the .proto file containing message definitions"},"513":{"id":"/docs/connectors/sdk-21","page_id":"/docs/connectors/sdk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/connectors/sdk#source-configuration","content":"message_type: Fully qualified name of the protobuf message type to use"},"514":{"id":"/docs/connectors/sdk-22","page_id":"/docs/connectors