umns (default: true)"],[2145,"include_metadata: Wrap results with metadata (default: true)"],[1699,"include_origin_timestamp"],[1754,"include_origin_timestamp: Include original message timestamp (default: true)"],[2067,"Incremental Data Processing: Track last processed timestamp to avoid reprocessing data"],[1289,"index"],[1511,"Index caching can be configured per strategy: \"all\" (all indexes in memory), \"open_segment\" (only the active segment cached, the default), or \"none\" (on-demand disk reads)."],[1253,"Index caching can be configured via the cache_indexes setting:"],[1630,"index_mapping: Index mapping configuration"],[1625,"index: Target index name"],[1775,"index: The index configuration using YAML, as described in the Quickwit index configuration docs"],[1194,"Indexes"],[1261,"Indexes are loaded on-demand from disk"],[770,"Ingress - optional ingress for HTTP access"],[846,"Inherits from its transport"],[1974,"initial_mtu - the initial MTU size (default: 1200)"],[2140,"initial_offset: Starting value for the tracking column"],[295,"Initiate view change"],[160,"Installation"],[1834,"Installation"],[1855,"Installation"],[1874,"Installation"],[1905,"Installation"],[1928,"Installation"],[1957,"Instead of providing the configuration for the client, you can use the connection string. It's a string that contains all the necessary information to connect to the Iggy API with only a single caveat, as it does support TCP protocol only for now. Here's the basic example:"],[438,"Internally, dlopen2 provides a safe and efficient way of loading the plugins via C FFI."],[2168,"interval"],[1994,"Intro"],[33,"Introduction"],[367,"Introduction"],[556,"Introduction"],[774,"Introduction"],[1446,"io_uring and compio"],[1485,"io_uring is completion-based - you submit I/O requests to a submission queue (SQ), and the kernel completes them and places results in a completion queue (CQ). Both queues are lock-free ring buffers shared between user space and kernel. This is fundamentall