: Column to track for incremental updates (default: \"id\")"],[1484,"Traditional async runtimes like tokio use epoll which is readiness-based - you ask the kernel \"is this file descriptor ready?\" and then perform the I/O yourself. The Linux kernel considers regular files \"always ready\" for epoll, which means tokio has to outsource file I/O to a blocking thread pool (up to 512 threads). This does not scale well."],[298,"Transfer state for view change"],[496,"Transform Options"],[380,"Transformations"],[371,"Transforms"],[1669,"Transforms"],[386,"Transforms run inside the runtime process, not inside the plugins. They are applied after decoding for sources (before sending to Iggy) and after consuming from Iggy for sinks (before forwarding to the external system)."],[521,"Transforms: Convert between protobuf and other formats (JSON, Text)"],[10,"Transport"],[565,"Transport"],[608,"Transport"],[837,"Transport"],[1152,"Transport encryption (TLS)"],[195,"Transport protocol (tcp, quic, http, websocket)"],[783,"Transport protocols"],[606,"Transport selection via scheme:"],[2062,"Troubleshooting"],[1693,"true"],[1697,"true"],[1701,"true"],[1709,"true"],[1816,"true"],[248,"Type"],[389,"Type"],[1216,"Type"],[1516,"Type"],[1672,"Type"],[1811,"Type"],[2165,"Type"],[1224,"u128"],[1524,"u128"],[254,"u32"],[257,"u32"],[1240,"u32"],[1244,"u32"],[1540,"u32"],[1544,"u32"],[1688,"u32"],[1716,"u32"],[2181,"u32"],[260,"u64"],[263,"u64"],[1220,"u64"],[1228,"u64"],[1232,"u64"],[1236,"u64"],[1248,"u64"],[1520,"u64"],[1528,"u64"],[1532,"u64"],[1536,"u64"],[1548,"u64"],[2173,"u64"],[251,"u8"],[252,"Unique identifier for this replica"],[1225,"Unique message ID (UUIDv4)"],[1525,"Unique message ID (UUIDv4)"],[1984,"Unless you need to provide a specific implementation of the client-side Encryptor, Partitioner or adjust some other settings, you should be good to go with the connection string. On the other hand, you can always make use of IggyClientBuilder::from_connection_string() to extend the